      • equals

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object other)
        Checks if two features are equal to each other. Two features are deeply equal if they have the same base and the same phenotype.

        This is an unorthodox equals method to be used implicitly in Organism class's setAttributesFromEnvironment() method, and Environment's filter() method. It ensures that the multipliers that is returned by the getMultipliers() method of EnvironmentalCondition class is properly multiplied with the organism's correct features' multipliers. To do this, this method implicitly converts the genotype into a phenotype and then compares the phenotypes of the two features in question.

        Overrides:
        equals in class java.lang.Object
        Parameters:
        other - the other object to be compared with this one
        Returns:
        returns true if the other object is a Feature that is the same type and bears the same phenotype as this one.
        See Also:
        Organism, World, Environment, EnvironmentalCondition
